list.item: Client will engage with CST case manager throughout housing search. Client will provide her housing requests to CST, participate in housing search, attend apartment viewings (as scheduled), and collaborate with CST to complete necessary paperwork in order to secure housing (ie. rental application, HACC forms etc.). Client will maintain her ADL's at a level that is appropriate for independent living in the community.
Client will take steps toward attending school including: finding a school she would like to attend, picking a program of interest and finding funding to pay for schooling.
Client will take steps toward obtaining employment including researching job postings she is interested in, completing and updating her resume and filling out job applications.
To ensure client has access to medical/psychiatric services as needed to promote overall health and wellbeing.

tr.td: Client reports wanting to obtain her own apartment. Client states "I wanna move out."
Client reports wanting to obtain her GED. Client states "I wanna go back to school."
Client reports wanting to obtain employment once she moves out of the NH. Client states "I wanna get a job."
Decreased frequency and intensity of psychotic and other severe mental illness symptoms.

CST will assist and support Levonne in searching for, obtaining, and/or maintaining housing at a level of independence appropriate for her. CST will assist and support Levonne in applying for housing and in obtaining all appropriate financial assistance (re: utilities, rent etc.). CST will assist Levonne in obtaining furniture and necessities, as needed. CST will assist and support Levonne in developing a budget to allow her to maintain stable housing. CST will assist and support Levonne in complying with lease terms/rules. CST will communicate with landlord as needed (re: issues that may arise regarding Levonne's living arrangement, Levonne's unit, etc.).

As Levonne feels ready, CST can assist, support and educate her on resources in the community and can link her to educational opportunities. CST will support and encourage Levonne as she pursues her goal of returning to school, including supporting and assisting her as she researches programs and a means of financing her education.

As Levonne feels ready, CST can assist, support and educate her on resources in the community and can link her to employment opportunities. CST will support and encourage Levonne as she pursues her goal of obtaining employment, including supporting and assisting her as she researches potential jobs.

Nurse will refer client to primary care physician (if needed). Nurse will complete medical paperwork, and complete pre-authorizations for public or private entitlements. Will assist with application for pharmaceutical patient assistance program.
Psychiatrist will evaluate & monitor medications to assist client with maintaining stability.

Nurse will provide individual or group services related to self-management of diabetes, smoking, and weight management. Nurse will assist patient with any medical/psychiatric paperwork (i.e., choosing health plans) to ensure client receives most effective services. Nurse will assist patient in making appointments with their PCP and encourages patient to make calls on their own behalf.

Nurse will engage in professional communication with other provider staff re: client's clinical condition (vitals, lab results, medications, side effects) and progress towards treatment goals. Nurse will make referrals to primary care physicians or ER, if warranted.
